                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d723">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">767.68119/26</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chief of the Division of Near Eastern Affairs, Department
                        of State</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Dulles</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the Under Secretary of State</hi> (<persName
                        type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Phillips</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1922-09-19">
                            <hi rend="italic">September 19, 1922</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Mr. Phillips</hi>: In the course of an informal discussion
                    with regard to the situation in the Near East, Craigie, First Secretary of the
                    British Embassy, asked me whether, in my opinion, there was any chance of this
                    Government’s consenting to send a representative to take part in the Near
                    Eastern settlement. I said that I could not answer this but that I would be glad
                    to mention to Mr. Phillips that the question had been raised. Craigie said that
                    he did not wish to make an official inquiry but that it would be helpful if at
                    any time we could give them an informal hint as to whether we would consent to
                    be represented. He left with me the impression that there might be some
                    hesitation about sending us an invitation to the Conference if it were unlikely
                    to be favorably considered.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>A[<hi rend="smallcaps">llen</hi>] W. D[<hi rend="smallcaps"
                        >ulles</hi>]</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
